<font color="#FF0000">HAVE YOU HAD ENOUGH?</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jun 10 23:02:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was channel surfing on my tv and I came across the film,<br>
The Killing Field.  I had seen it before. Before this site, for sure. Before the leading man, Dr. Someone (I am terrible at names, let alone Cambodian-Asian names) was murdered on the mean streets of Los Angeles. Case still remains unsolved. Was it political payback or a random act of robbery? No one yet knows.  What I do know is the movie hit me across the face this time, THIS TIME, perhaps because I am different than the last time I saw this film.  Less critical of other people and cultures, more accepting.  More understanding of my brothers who happened to be vets, and my sisters, who happened to be protestors, and of myself, who happened to be a C.O.<br><br>
Have we finally said it all, I ask?  I don't think so.  As long as men (and women) think and agree that no war is a good war, as long as we all agree to not let our children learn the horrible lessons we learned, will we grow silent.<br><br>
So Lads, and Lassies, where are you these days?  Have you spoken your peace and are done? Have you found peace in your heart? If so, tell us all, tell us for those that have not.<br><br>
de doc
